# Ollama Modelfile for docint's bge-m3 embedding profile.
#
# Ollama serves bge-m3 with ``num_ctx=2048`` by default, which caps each
# embedding request at a 2048-token window regardless of bge-m3's real
# 8192-token model capacity. Operators who want docint's pre-embed
# re-splitter to use the full window can bake a custom tag with this
# Modelfile:
#
#     ollama pull bge-m3
#     ollama create docint-bge-m3 -f deploy/Modelfile.bge-m3
#
# Then, in ``.env``:
#
#     EMBED_MODEL=docint-bge-m3
#     EMBED_CTX_TOKENS=8192
#
# docint's worker side verifies every outbound payload against the
# configured ``EMBED_CTX_TOKENS`` using the real bge-m3 tokenizer, so as
# long as the ollama-side ``num_ctx`` and the env-side
# ``EMBED_CTX_TOKENS`` agree, ingestion stays correct.

FROM bge-m3
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192
